Russian Stocks: Novolipetsk Steel, Raspadskaya, Razgulay Group

-- B y   M a r k   S w e e t m a n   a n d   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-04-13T15:38:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/russian-equity-movers-sberbank-raspadskaya-surgutneftegas.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  gained 0.6
percent to 1,809.83 at the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, the first
increase this week. The dollar-denominated RTS Index was little
changed at 2,062.47.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Novolipetsk Steel (NLMK RX), Russian billionaire
 Vladimir Lisin ’s steelmaker lost 1.5 percent to 113.49 rubles,
extending its decline this year to 22 percent after Credit
Suisse Group AG cut the stock to “underperform” from
“neutral.”  OAO  Raspadskaya (RASP)   advanced 1 percent to 197.77
rubles, the biggest rally since April 8. The coal producer said
2010 net income more than doubled to $245 million and first-
quarter output increased by 39 percent in comparison with the
fourth quarter.  OAO  Razgulay Group (GRAZ)  , a Russian sugar and rice
producer, climbed for the first day in three, adding 0.6 percent
to 66.83 rubles after board member Dmitry Shteinsapir said
yesterday the company is in talks to sell some assets to United
Grain Co.,  Russia ’s state-owned grain trader.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Sweetman in Moscow at 
